Lombard Odier Asset Management Switzerland Sa Has Raised Morgan Stanley (MS) Stake By $12.26 Million, Garmin LTD Has 1.35 Sentiment


					
						July 21, 2017 - By Clifton Ray

Garmin Ltd. and subsidiaries offer global positioning system (GPS) navigation and wireless devices and applications. The company has market cap of $9.64 billion. The Firm operates through five divisions. It has a 14.78 P/E ratio. It offers a range of auto navigation products, as well as a range of products and applications designed for the mobile GPS market.







Lombard Odier Asset Management Switzerland Sa increased Morgan Stanley (MS) stake by 331.82% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Lombard Odier Asset Management Switzerland Sa acquired 292,000 shares as Morgan Stanley (MS)’s stock declined 9.43%. The Lombard Odier Asset Management Switzerland Sa holds 380,000 shares with $16.06 million value, up from 88,000 last quarter. Morgan Stanley now has $85.98 billion valuation. The stock increased 0.17% or $0.08 on July 21, reaching $46.59. About 7.76M shares traded. Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) has risen 57.08% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 40.38% the S&P500.
Among 27 analysts covering Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS), 15 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 12 Hold. Therefore 56% are positive. Morgan Stanley had 65 analyst reports since July 21, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was maintained by Barclays Capital on Wednesday, April 6 with “Equalweight”. RBC Capital Markets maintained the stock with “Buy” rating in Friday, July 7 report. The rating was maintained by Macquarie Research with “Neutral” on Tuesday, October 20. The firm has “Buy” rating by Guggenheim given on Thursday, October 20. The company was maintained on Monday, June 19 by BMO Capital Markets. The rating was maintained by Oppenheimer on Wednesday, July 19 with “Hold”. The firm has “Outperform” rating by JMP Securities given on Thursday, October 8. Argus Research maintained it with “Buy” rating and $40.0 target in Friday, September 4 report. The firm has “Neutral” rating by Atlantic Securities given on Wednesday, December 21. Vining Sparks maintained the shares of MS in report on Friday, April 21 with “Strong-Buy” rating.
Investors sentiment increased to 1.15 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.21, from 0.94 in 2016Q3. It increased, as 53 investors sold MS shares while 267 reduced holdings. 132 funds opened positions while 236 raised stakes. 1.58 billion shares or 1.64% more from 1.56 billion shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Athena Advsrs Ltd Liability reported 9,095 shares. Cypress Management Ltd Company (Wy) invested 0% in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). 248,462 were accumulated by Carlson Cap Lp. Wesbanco National Bank Inc stated it has 114,892 shares. Nikko Asset Americas Inc has 7,500 shares. Blair William And Il reported 64,453 shares stake. Geode Cap Management Lc has invested 0.26% in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). Federated Inc Pa has invested 0.15% in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). Kistler invested 0.01% in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). 142,670 were reported by Shell Asset. California-based Advisor Prtn has invested 0.39% in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). Guardian Life Insurance Company Of America has 0.03% invested in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). Fjarde Ap stated it has 0.31% in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). Nippon Life Insurance has invested 0.05% in Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS). Louisiana State Employees Retirement System accumulated 90,700 shares.
Since January 1, 0001, it had 0 insider purchases, and 3 selling transactions for $16.02 million activity. 
The stock increased 0.51% or $0.26 during the last trading session, reaching $51.59. About 533,218 shares traded. Garmin Ltd. (GRMN) has risen 28.63% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 11.93% the S&P500.
Ratings analysis reveals 0 of Garmin’s analysts are positive. Out of 2 Wall Street analysts rating Garmin, 0 give it “Buy”, 1 “Sell” rating, while 1 recommend “Hold”. GRMN was included in 2 notes of analysts from August 22, 2016. The firm earned “Mkt Perform” rating on Monday, August 22 by Raymond James. The firm earned “Sell” rating on Wednesday, August 24 by Goldman Sachs.








By Clifton Ray
