Carolina Minio-Paluello Ph.D.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 25, 2017 9:54 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Lombard Odier Asset Management (Europe) Limited



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Carolina   Minio-Paluello Ph.D.Global Head of Sales and Solutions, Lombard Odier Asset Management (Europe) LimitedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 0 different industries.----
Background

		Dr. Carolina Minio-Paluello, Ph.D. is the Global Head of Sales and Solutions at Lombard Odier Asset Management (Europe) Limited and Lombard Odier Investment Managers Holding SA and previously served as Deputy Chief Investment Officer. Dr. Minio-Paluello builds on the business' pioneering risk-based approach to portfolio construction for institutional clients at Lombard Odier Asset Management. She joined the firm in 2013. Prior to joining the firm, Dr. Minio-Paluello ... served as Managing Director and Head of Quantitative Resources Group at Goldman Sachs Asset Management International Ltd. She served as the Head of EMEA for Equity and Private Investor Solutions at Citigroup Investments Inc. Dr. Minio-Paluello served at JP Morgan Investments. She served as Managing Director at Goldman Sachs Asset Management, L.P. and served as its Portfolio Manager of Product Strategy and Quantitative Resources since May 2000. In November 2000, Dr. Minio-Paluello joined the Global Fixed Income and Active Equity teams to manage the global balanced product. In December 2001, she was responsible for quantitative products in Europe and Asia ex-Japan. Dr. Minio-Paluello holds a Ph.D. in Finance from the London Business School, a Masters in Finance from Université Catholique de Louvain, and a B.A. degree in Economics from Universite Libre de Bruxelles in Belgium.Read Full Background




